verses.text_plain: Then again Abraham took a wife, and her name was Keturah.
verses.verse_html: 1Then again Abraham took a wife, and her name was Keturah.

verses.text_plain: And she bare him Zimran, and Jokshan, and Medan, and Midian, and Ishbak, and Shuah.
verses.verse_html: 2And she bare him Zimran, and Jokshan, and Medan, and Midian, and Ishbak, and Shuah.

verses.text_plain: And Jokshan begat Sheba, and Dedan. And the sons of Dedan were Asshurim, and Letushim, and Leummim.
verses.verse_html: 3And Jokshan begat Sheba, and Dedan. And the sons of Dedan were Asshurim, and Letushim, and Leummim.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Midian; Ephah, and Epher, and Hanoch, and Abida, and Eldaah. All these were the children of Keturah.
verses.verse_html: 4And the sons of Midian; Ephah, and Epher, and Hanoch, and Abida, and Eldaah. All these were the children of Keturah.

verses.text_plain: And Abraham gave all that he had unto Isaac.
verses.verse_html: 5And Abraham gave all that he had unto Isaac.

tokens.text: all that he had unto Isaac

verses.text_plain: But unto the sons of the concubines, which Abraham had, Abraham gave gifts, and sent them away from Isaac his son, while he yet lived, eastward, unto the east country.
verses.verse_html: 6But unto the sons of the concubines, which Abraham had, Abraham gave gifts, and sent them away from Isaac his son, while he yet lived, eastward, unto the east country.

verses.text_plain: And these are the days of the years of Abraham’s life which he lived, an hundred threescore and fifteen years.
verses.verse_html: 7And these are the days of the years of Abraham’s life which he lived, an hundred threescore and fifteen years.

verses.text_plain: Then Abraham gave up the ghost, and died in a good old age, an old man, and full of years; and was gathered to his people.
verses.verse_html: 8Then Abraham gave up the ghost, and died in a good old age, an old man, and full of years; and was gathered to his people.

verses.text_plain: And his sons Isaac and Ishmael buried him in the cave of Machpelah, in the field of Ephron the son of Zohar the Hittite, which is before Mamre;
verses.verse_html: 9And his sons Isaac and Ishmael buried him in the cave of Machpelah, in the field of Ephron the son of Zohar the Hittite, which is before Mamre;

verses.text_plain: The field which Abraham purchased of the sons of Heth: there was Abraham buried, and Sarah his wife.
verses.verse_html: 10The field which Abraham purchased of the sons of Heth: there was Abraham buried, and Sarah his wife.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass after the death of Abraham, that God blessed his son Isaac; and Isaac dwelt by the well Lahai–roi.
verses.verse_html: 11And it came to pass after the death of Abraham, that God blessed his son Isaac; and Isaac dwelt by the well Lahai–roi.

tokens.text: And it came to pass after

verses.text_plain: Now these are the generations of Ishmael, Abraham’s son, whom Hagar the Egyptian, Sarah’s handmaid, bare unto Abraham:
verses.verse_html: 12Now these are the generations of Ishmael, Abraham’s son, whom Hagar the Egyptian, Sarah’s handmaid, bare unto Abraham:

verses.text_plain: And these are the names of the sons of Ishmael, by their names, according to their generations: the firstborn of Ishmael, Nebajoth; and Kedar, and Adbeel, and Mibsam,
verses.verse_html: 13And these are the names of the sons of Ishmael, by their names, according to their generations: the firstborn of Ishmael, Nebajoth; and Kedar, and Adbeel, and Mibsam,

verses.text_plain: And Mishma, and Dumah, and Massa,
verses.verse_html: 14And Mishma, and Dumah, and Massa,

verses.text_plain: Hadar, and Tema, Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah:
verses.verse_html:
15Hadar, and Tema, Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah: ▼
▼ Hadar: or, Hadad

verses.text_plain: These are the sons of Ishmael, and these are their names, by their towns, and by their castles; twelve princes according to their nations.
verses.verse_html: 16These are the sons of Ishmael, and these are their names, by their towns, and by their castles; twelve princes according to their nations.

verses.text_plain: And these are the years of the life of Ishmael, an hundred and thirty and seven years: and he gave up the ghost and died; and was gathered unto his people.
verses.verse_html: 17And these are the years of the life of Ishmael, an hundred and thirty and seven years: and he gave up the ghost and died; and was gathered unto his people.

tokens.text: and he gave up the ghost

verses.text_plain: And they dwelt from Havilah unto Shur, that is before Egypt, as thou goest toward Assyria: and he died in the presence of all his brethren.
verses.verse_html:
18And they dwelt from Havilah unto Shur, that is before Egypt, as thou goest toward Assyria: and he died in the presence of all his brethren. ▼
▼ died: Heb. fell

verses.text_plain: And these are the generations of Isaac, Abraham’s son: Abraham begat Isaac:
verses.verse_html: 19And these are the generations of Isaac, Abraham’s son: Abraham begat Isaac:

verses.text_plain: And Isaac was forty years old when he took Rebekah to wife, the daughter of Bethuel the Syrian of Padan–aram, the sister to Laban the Syrian.
verses.verse_html: 20And Isaac was forty years old when he took Rebekah to wife, the daughter of Bethuel the Syrian of Padan–aram, the sister to Laban the Syrian.

verses.text_plain: And Isaac intreated the Lord for his wife, because she was barren: and the Lord was intreated of him, and Rebekah his wife conceived.
verses.verse_html: 21And Isaac intreated the Lord for his wife, because she was barren: and the Lord was intreated of him, and Rebekah his wife conceived.

verses.text_plain: And the children struggled together within her; and she said, If it be so, why am I thus? And she went to enquire of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 22And the children struggled together within her; and she said, If it be so, why am I thus? And she went to enquire of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord said unto her, Two nations are in thy womb, and two manner of people shall be separated from thy bowels; and the one people shall be stronger than the other people; and the elder shall serve the younger.
verses.verse_html: 23And the Lord said unto her, Two nations are in thy womb, and two manner of people shall be separated from thy bowels; and the one people shall be stronger than the other people; and the elder shall serve the younger.

verses.text_plain: And when her days to be delivered were fulfilled, behold, there were twins in her womb.
verses.verse_html: 24And when her days to be delivered were fulfilled, behold, there were twins in her womb.

verses.text_plain: And the first came out red, all over like an hairy garment; and they called his name Esau.
verses.verse_html: 25And the first came out red, all over like an hairy garment; and they called his name Esau.

verses.text_plain: And after that came his brother out, and his hand took hold on Esau’s heel; and his name was called Jacob: and Isaac was threescore years old when she bare them.
verses.verse_html: 26And after that came his brother out, and his hand took hold on Esau’s heel; and his name was called Jacob: and Isaac was threescore years old when she bare them.

verses.text_plain: And the boys grew: and Esau was a cunning hunter, a man of the field; and Jacob was a plain man, dwelling in tents.
verses.verse_html: 27And the boys grew: and Esau was a cunning hunter, a man of the field; and Jacob was a plain man, dwelling in tents.

verses.text_plain: And Isaac loved Esau, because he did eat of his venison: but Rebekah loved Jacob.
verses.verse_html:
28And Isaac loved Esau, because he did eat of his venison: but Rebekah loved Jacob. ▼
▼ he…: Heb. venison was in his mouth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ he…: Heb. venison was in his mouth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ he…: Heb. venison was in his mouth

verses.text_plain: And Jacob sod pottage: and Esau came from the field, and he was faint:
verses.verse_html: 29And Jacob sod pottage: and Esau came from the field, and he was faint:

verses.text_plain: And Esau said to Jacob, Feed me, I pray thee, with that same red pottage; for I am faint: therefore was his name called Edom.
verses.verse_html:
30And Esau said to Jacob, Feed me, I pray thee, with that same red pottage; for I am faint: therefore was his name called Edom. ▼
▼ with…: Heb. with that red, with that red pottage
 , ▼
▼ Edom: that is Red

footnotes.body_text: ▼ with…: Heb. with that red, with that red pottage
footnotes.body_html: ▼ with…: Heb. with that red, with that red pottage
▼ Edom: that is Red

verses.text_plain: And Jacob said, Sell me this day thy birthright.
verses.verse_html: 31And Jacob said, Sell me this day thy birthright.

verses.text_plain: And Esau said, Behold, I am at the point to die: and what profit shall this birthright do to me?
verses.verse_html:
32And Esau said, Behold, I am at the point to die: and what profit shall this birthright do to me? ▼
▼ at…: Heb. going to die

tokens.text: and what profit shall this birthright

footnotes.body_html: ▼ at…: Heb. going to die

verses.text_plain: And Jacob said, Swear to me this day; and he sware unto him: and he sold his birthright unto Jacob.
verses.verse_html: 33And Jacob said, Swear to me this day; and he sware unto him: and he sold his birthright unto Jacob.

verses.text_plain: Then Jacob gave Esau bread and pottage of lentiles; and he did eat and drink, and rose up, and went his way: thus Esau despised his birthright.
verses.verse_html: 34Then Jacob gave Esau bread and pottage of lentiles; and he did eat and drink, and rose up, and went his way: thus Esau despised his birthright.
